# cs3380

This repository contains code and resources for the CS3380 research project at Western University, conducted under the guidance of Dr. Jackson 2bears (Jackson Leween).

## Project Overview

This project explores the intersection of sound, vibration, and visual form through the lens of cymatics. It includes tools to extract sound features such as fundamental frequency and amplitude from audio files, and a real-time simulation that visualizes these properties using shaders. The system integrates Max/MSP, Python, and OpenGL to create dynamic, sound-reactive visual patterns inspired by traditional yantras and the science of cymatics.

## Folder Structure

```
cs3380/
├── data/                   # Audio and data files
├── src/                    # Source code
│   ├── shader/             # Shaders: fragment_shader.glsl and vertex_shader.vs
│   └── live_chladni_gl.py  # Real-time 
├── chladniPatch.maxpat     # Max/MSP patch for 
├── README.md               # Project documentation
```

## Requirements

moderngl
glfw
numpy
librosa
matplotlib
python-osc
soundfile
scipy
pillow


Install dependencies with:
```sh
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

# downloaded 
pip install moderngl glfw numpy librosa matplotlib python-osc soundfile scipy pillow


## Usage

Example to run the audio analysis script:
```sh
python src/sound_extract.py
```

